<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571544>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Atheta (Dimetrota) machonryongica. A: antenna; B: male abdominal tergite VIII (dorsal aspect); C: male abdominal sternite VIII (ventral aspect); D: female abdominal tergite VIII (dorsal aspect); E: female abdominal sternite VIII (ventral aspect); F: median lobe of aedeagus (lateral aspect); G: median lobe of aedeagus (ventral aspect); H: paramere (lateral aspect); I: spermatheca. Scales = 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6571544/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571556>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Atheta (Dimetrota) ovata sp. nov. A: male abdominal tergite VIII (dorsal aspect); B: posterior margin of male abdominal tergite VIII (dorsal aspect); C: microsculpture of male abdominal tergite VIII (dorsal aspect); D: male abdominal sternite VIII (ventral aspect); E: female abdominal tergite VIII (dorsal aspect); F: female abdominal sternite VIII (ventral aspect); G: posterior margin of female abdominal sternite VIII (ventral aspect)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6571556/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571564>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Atheta (Dimetrota) yamamotoi. A: antenna; B: male abdominal tergite VIII (dorsal aspect); C: male abdominal sternite VIII (ventral aspect); D: female abdominal tergite VIII (dorsal aspect); E: female abdominal sternite VIII (ventral aspect); F: median lobe of aedeagus (lateral aspect); G: median lobe of aedeagus (ventral aspect); H: paramere (lateral aspect); I: spermatheca. Scales = 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6571564/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

